{
  "texts": [
    "Convolutional neural network (CNN) models have shown to be quite successful in complicated object recognition and classification tasks in recent years.",
    "Their main advantage is their capacity to extract sturdy characteristics resistant to varying degrees of distortion and light.",
    "DL has not yet addressed some histopathology issues, despite the fact that DL has shown remarkable results in several disciplines for identifying scenes and classifying objects.",
    "First, the histopathology field is constrained by the numerous data with labels needed for deep CNN training.",
    "Second, deep networks struggle to generalize successfully for new data after training on little data, making them susceptible to \"overfitting. \""
  ]
}